Carr Lake Community Day Dashboard DA Summary

Report Purpose

This report is created to assist Carr Lake Community Day in reflecting on the student groups whose indicators led to Differentiated Assistance for Salinas Union High.

Qualifying Groups

Differentiated Assistance is determined by the California Dashboard. Colors reflect the latest available status from 2022. For all graphs, the darker the color the lower the status.

The graphic below shows the color for each student group for each indicator from the California 2022 Dashboard.

California Dashboard 2022

The graph below displays which student groups qualified Salinas Union High to be eligible for Differentiated Assistance. Moreover, for each student group it shows which Priority Areas and associated indicators met qualification criteria.

As a reminder, COEs must offer differentiated assistance to a school district if any student group meets the criteria for two or more LCFF priorities according to California Education Code Section 52071(c). Californiaâs System of Support

For Carr Lake Community Day, the below graph shows how at the school level their student groups did at the school level which contributed to Salinas Union High as an LEA overall. Note this also includes student groups with 11 to 29 students in them to provide a fuller picture even if those groups are not used for state accountability calculations.

Status Needed to Avoid Red in 2023

This section estimates the limits for indicators to receive an orange or higher color next year on the 2023 Dashboard. The thresholds below are based on the 5x5 grids last approved by the State Board of Education and the number of students in the 2022 calculation. State policies may change and the student counts may shift. Only student groups in DA and their qualifying indicators for Salinas Union High are included below and only if they are in the lowest status for Carr Lake Community Day. The thresholds represent the numbers for Carr Lake Community Day.
